Paper: hep-th/0105226

Date: 2001-05-22

Title: Negative Probability and Uncertainty Relations

Authors: Thomas Curtright and Cosmas Zachos

Comments: RevTeX, 4 pages

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A16 (2001) 2381-2385

A concise derivation of all uncertainty relations is given entirely withinthe context of phase-space quantization, without recourse to operator methods,to the direct use of Weyl's correspondence, or to marginal distributions of xand p.